---
/**
 * advanced-ai-systems/0001 · Figure 4 — "Failure modes unique to multi-agent"
 * (Module 3): cascading errors, context fragmentation, cost/latency blowup.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/advanced-ai-systems/lessons/0001-multi-agent-systems-
 * when-and-when-not.html. Uses the shared arrowhead marker #arwR (defined by
 * <Fig0>). Kept as an .astro component (not inline MDX) for reliable raw-SVG
 * rendering. SVG anchor id (r4b) matches the source DOM + the #s4 footnote.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 240"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Three failure modes unique to multi-agent: cascading errors where a wrong partial poisons the synthesis, context fragmentation where no agent sees the whole, and cost blowups where tokens scale with agents times turns times retries."
    >
        <text x="320" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Failure modes unique to multi-agent</text
        >

        <!-- cascading errors -->
        <rect
            x="24"
            y="34"
            width="190"
            height="170"
            rx="10"
            fill="#fbecec"
            stroke="#9a2417"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="119" y="54" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >1 · Cascading errors</text
        >
        <rect x="44" y="66" width="68" height="24" rx="5" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#9a2417"
        ></rect><text x="78" y="82" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#9a2417"
            >bad partial</text
        >
        <line x1="112" y1="78" x2="138" y2="78" stroke="#9a2417" marker-end="url(#arwR)"></line>
        <rect x="138" y="66" width="58" height="24" rx="5" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#9a2417"
        ></rect><text x="167" y="82" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#9a2417"
            >trusted</text
        >
        <line x1="119" y1="92" x2="119" y2="112" stroke="#9a2417" marker-end="url(#arwR)"></line>
        <rect x="44" y="114" width="152" height="26" rx="5" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#9a2417"></rect>
        <text x="120" y="131" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#9a2417"
            >confident wrong synthesis</text
        >
        <text
            x="119"
            y="162"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="7.5"
            font-style="italic"
            fill="#9a2417">error compounds across steps</text
        >
        <text x="119" y="182" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >Fix: validate at the join</text
        >
        <text x="119" y="195" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7" fill="#6b675f"
            >don't blindly trust partials</text
        >

        <!-- context fragmentation -->
        <rect
            x="224"
            y="34"
            width="192"
            height="170"
            rx="10"
            fill="#fbecec"
            stroke="#9a2417"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="320" y="54" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >2 · Context fragmentation</text
        >
        <rect x="244" y="66" width="50" height="26" rx="5" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#9a2417"
        ></rect><text x="269" y="83" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7" fill="#9a2417">slice A</text
        >
        <rect x="299" y="66" width="50" height="26" rx="5" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#9a2417"
        ></rect><text x="324" y="83" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7" fill="#9a2417">slice B</text
        >
        <rect x="354" y="66" width="50" height="26" rx="5" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#9a2417"
        ></rect><text x="379" y="83" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7" fill="#9a2417">slice C</text
        >
        <text x="320" y="112" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#9a2417"
            >no one sees the whole</text
        >
        <text x="320" y="130" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#9a2417"
            >&rarr; duplicate &amp; contradict</text
        >
        <text
            x="320"
            y="162"
            text-anchor="middle"
            font-size="7.5"
            font-style="italic"
            fill="#9a2417">slices don't add up to the picture</text
        >
        <text x="320" y="182" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >Fix: decide shared vs isolated</text
        >
        <text x="320" y="195" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7" fill="#6b675f"
            >share the goal; isolate the rest</text
        >

        <!-- cost blowup -->
        <rect
            x="426"
            y="34"
            width="190"
            height="170"
            rx="10"
            fill="#fbecec"
            stroke="#9a2417"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <text x="521" y="54" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >3 · Cost / latency blowup</text
        >
        <rect x="446" y="66" width="150" height="50" rx="6" fill="#ffffff" stroke="#9a2417"></rect>
        <text x="521" y="86" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >tokens scale with</text
        >
        <text x="521" y="102" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#9a2417"
            >agents &times; turns &times; retries</text
        >
        <text x="521" y="138" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#9a2417"
            >runaway fan-out / chatty loops</text
        >
        <text x="521" y="156" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7" font-style="italic" fill="#6b675f"
            >multi-agent burns many&times; a chat turn (illustrative)</text
        >
        <text x="521" y="182" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >Fix: cap agents/turns/budget</text
        >
        <text x="521" y="195" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7" fill="#6b675f"
            >attribute spend · kill switch</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        None of these exist for a single agent — they're the price of coordination. Treat each as a
        distributed-systems failure: validate at the joins, define context boundaries, and bound the
        blast radius with caps and per-agent attribution.<sup><a href="#s4" id="r4b">4</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
